<dl id="n11122d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11122d">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11122d"> 122(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Charitable Infirmary / Jervis St. 1718</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">STORY OF STEEVENS HOSPITAL / A MONUMENTAL WORK / The History of Dr. Steevens&apos; Hospital, 1720-1920. By T. Percy C. Kirkpatrick, M.D., M.I.R.A. Pp. 414 (Dublin: The University Press. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>) <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> OUR OLDEST HOSPITALS / What is known now as <mark>Jervis St</mark>. Hospital has the distinction of being not alone the oldest of our modern Dublin Hospitals, but, with the exception of St. Bartholomew and St. Thomas in London, the oldest in the Three Kingdoms. Originally called the <mark>Charitable Infirmary, it was founded in 1718</mark> by a small group of Dublin surgeons at their own expense. <small> <a name="II7jul24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II7jul24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (7 July 1924) 4/2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
